June 15 Joint Committee Meets 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 11 (KCNA) -- A report on the meeting of the Preparatory Committee for Joint Functions of Koreans in the North, South and Overseas for Implementing the June 15 Joint Declaration (June 15 Joint Committee) was made public in Shenyang, China on Saturday.
 The report said:
 A meeting of the June 15 Joint Committee was held in Shenyang, China from Dec. 9 to 10 amid the expectation and interest of the public at home and abroad. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the meeting were a delegation of the north side's preparatory committee headed by its Chairman An Kyong Ho, a delegation of the south side's preparatory committee headed by its Chairman Paek Rak Chong and a delegation of the overseas side's preparatory committee led by its Co-Chairmen Kwak Tong Ui and Mun Tong Hwan. 
 The meeting recalled the fact that the committee successfully held grand festivals for national reunification in Pyongyang and Seoul in this significant year which greeted the 5th anniversary of the publication of the June 15 joint declaration and the 60th anniversary of the liberation of Korea to boost the atmosphere of national reconciliation, unity and reunification and make a great contribution to the nationwide movement for the  reunification.
 Delegates of the north and the south and overseas preparatory committees had an in-depth discussion on the need for the joint committee to vigorously conduct the reunification movement in the future to live up to great expectation and trust of the whole nation and perform its duty and role as permanent solidarity organization for the reunification movement and agreed on the following points: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
1. They decided to rename the  Preparatory Committee for Joint Functions of Koreans in the North, South and Overseas for Implementing the June 15 Joint Declaration the National Joint Committee for Implementing the June 15 Joint Declaration (June 15 National Joint Committee) as required by the developing reality. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The regional preparatory committees in the north and the south and overseas will accordingly be renamed the North Side's Committee, South Side's Committee and Overseas Side's Committee for Implementing the June 15 Joint Declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
2. They also decided to adopt and effectuate the Statute of the National Joint Committee for Implementing the June 15 Joint Declaration from Dec. 10 to more effectively operate the joint committee as a solidarity organization of the north and the south and overseas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
3. Delegates of the north and the south and overseas sides expressed unanimous views on consolidating the achievements made in the reunification movement this year and bringing about a fresh turn in the movement for national independent reunification by the concerted efforts of the nation in 2006, too, under the banner of the June 15 joint declaration.

U.S. Scenario for Preemptive Nuclear Attack on DPRK Blasted 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 11 (KCNA) -- The U. S. imperialists recently decided to deploy the latest carrier "George Washington" in their naval base in Yokosuka, Kanagawa Prefecture, Japan.  This was a revelation of their undisguised intention to mount a preemptive nuclear attack on the DPRK to invade and stifle it. 
 Rodong Sinmun Sunday says this in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  The U. S. imperialists have turned south Korea into the biggest nuclear base in the Far East to threaten the DPRK with nukes and find a pretext for mounting a preemptive nuclear attack on it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Having massively deployed their nuclear forces in south Korea, they openly disclosed their intention to launch a preemptive nuclear attack on the DPRK in the event of "contingency." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 When starting the Korean war, U.S. President Truman ordered to work out a criminal plan for using atomic bombs in the war. It was stipulated in the "guidelines for the security" of the U.S. troops in south Korea that nuclear weapons are bound to be used should a war break out in Korea. This goes to clearly prove that the U.S. imperialists' preemptive nuclear attack on the DPRK is an established fact. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. bellicose elements created serious nuclear crises on the Korean Peninsula in the 1990s and even in the new century. All of them were aimed at finding pretexts for mounting a preemptive nuclear attack on the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The present U.S. administration became more undisguised in its attempt at the preemptive nuclear attack on the DPRK. It suspended all dialogues and negotiations which had been under way in the period of the previous administration and listed the DPRK as a part of "an axis of evil" in its "State of the Union Address" for 2002. The U.S. also listed the DPRK as the target of its preemptive nuclear attack in March of the same year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As seen above, it is the unchangeable strategy and ambition of the U.S. imperialists to stifle the DPRK through a preemptive nuclear attack. It was none other than the U.S. that compelled the DPRK to bolster up its physical deterrent forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If the United States truly wants a solution to the DPRK-U. S. nuclear issue, it should drop the above-said reckless intention and take practical steps for the denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula.

"Rally on Human Rights Issue in North" Assailed in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 10 (KCNA) -- South Korean organizations including the South Headquarters of the National Alliance for the Country's Reunification, the Federation of south Korean Trade Unions, the south Korean Women's Association against the United States, the People for Achieving Peace and Reunification, the south Korean Council of Youth Organizations and the Pusan Solidarity for Implementing the South-North Joint Declaration and the chairperson of the south Korean Federation of University Student Councils and others in commentaries and statements issued on Dec. 6 and 7 denounced a "rally on the human rights issue in the north" in Seoul. 
 The commentaries and statements termed the U.S. administration-sponsored rally a farce intended to create an atmosphere hostile to the north in the south under the pretext of the "human rights issue" and fool the Koreans and other peace-loving people of the world desirous of the implementation of the June 15 joint declaration and the joint statement adopted at the six-party talks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They charged that the call for the rally and the "human rights issue in the north" were based on sheer fabrications and lies. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The commentaries and statements strongly demanded an immediate cancellation of the plan to hold the rally designed to incite confrontation with the north.

S. Korean GNP Gentries' Hooliganism under Fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 10 (KCNA) -- The worst anti-reunification elements in south Korea committed such despicable vandalism as completely destroying the graveyard of unconverted long-term prisoners in Pogwang Temple, Phaju City, Kyonggi Province on Dec. 5.
 In this regard Rodong Sinmun Saturday in a signed commentary says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The unconverted long-term prisoners deserve to be praised by society and the people as patriotic martyrs for reunification as they dedicated themselves to the country and the Korean nation. However, those elements committed double murder of those prisoners. They are the ruffians utterly indifferent to the country and the nation and bereft of ethics. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The recent vandalism was instigated and wirepulled by none other than the GNP, a group of wicked anti-reunification conservative elements. The area devoted to honoring unconverted long-term prisoners has become an object of argument due to "the assertion about ideology and political coloring" since it was built by a religious organization of south Korea in May. This was attributable to the far-fetched assertion and provocation on the part of the ultra-right conservatives including the GNP. Some days before the occurrence of the vandalism, Kang Jae Sop, floor leader of the GNP, taking issue with the graveyard of unconverted long-term prisoners, talked nonsense at a meeting of the party leadership that it was little short of totally negating the "nature of the system" to praise the unconverted long-term prisoners "who were operatives sent to the south or guerillas" as patriotic martyrs for reunification. He was reported to have urged the authorities to take responsible measures in that regard. He went the lengths of asserting that the GNP would send lawmakers from the party to the spot to make an investigation into it in a bid to make the issue more complicated. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
This goes to prove that the hideous vandalism was perpetrated by fascist rascals at the undisguised instigation of the GNP and on its scenario. 
 The recent case teaches all Koreans a bitter lesson that if they allow the anti-reunification conservative forces including the GNP to go reckless, south Korea can never be in peace nor can the inter-Korean relations make smooth progress and the Korean nation is bound to undergo greater disasters.
 These forces can never go scot-free but face a stern judgment of the nation and history as they do not hesitate to trample down upon ethics and morality in a bid to cover up their crime-woven past and prolong their dirty remaining days.

Anti-DPRK Reckless Remarks of U.S. Ambassador in Seoul under Fire
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 10 (KCNA) -- The new U.S. ambassador in Seoul at a seminar held in Seoul on Dec. 7 dared slander the DPRK as a "criminal state."
 A spokesman for the Committee for the Peaceful Reunification of the Fatherland answering a question raised by KCNA on Dec. 9 in this regard said that the successive U.S. ambassadors in Seoul have never made such virulent outcries as those let loose by the new U.S. ambassador. What he uttered is an intolerable provocation and insult to the political system in the DPRK and its dignity and a very serious development that fundamentally overturned the spirit of the joint statement adopted at the fourth round of the six-party talks, the statement noted, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The recent case glaringly revealed once again the ulterior aggressive design of the U.S. to stifle the DPRK at any cost. This clearly proved that nothing has changed in its hostile policy toward the DPRK although it signed the joint statement at the six-party talks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As far as the criminal state touted by the U.S. is concerned, it is the biggest criminal state. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was none other than the U.S. that drenched the world in blood under the pretext of "combating terrorism" and inflicted the whole gamut of misfortune and disaster upon the Korean nation while keeping south Korea under its occupation for 60 years. Such arch criminal known worldwide dares slander the DPRK, a country dignified with independence and justice, as a "criminal state." This is like a thief crying "Stop the thief." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK will regard his utterance as a sort of provocative declaration of a war against the whole Korean nation and will mercilessly retaliate against it.
 South Koreans from all parties, groupings and strata should force him to stand in the Jongro Intersection, punish him in the name of the nation and immediately expel him from their land.

Koreans Called upon to Advance Guided by Idea of "By Our Nation Itself."
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 10 (KCNA) -- The idea of "By our nation itself", the basic idea in the era of independent reunification, serves as a motive force enabling all members of the nation to discharge their responsibility and role in the movement for national reunification and a source of strength for victoriously advancing the movement, says Rodong Sinmun today in a signed article.
 The Korean nation's movement for independent reunification has turned into a nationwide movement which involves all the Koreans, be they persons in authority or common people, irrespective of their ideology, political views and religious beliefs, the article says, adding: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It has become a major trend of the history of the nation to advance guided by the idea of "By our nation itself." 
 The historic June 15 joint declaration serves as a landmark for national reunification in the 21st century as it is a declaration on the independent reunification of the nation in which the Koreans in the north and the south committed themselves to solve the issue of national reunification independently by their concerted efforts. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The basic spirit of the joint declaration is the idea of "By our nation itself." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If Koreans are to discharge their responsibility and role in the issue of reunification, they should unite as one among other things. They have improved the inter-Korean relations and advanced the movement for national reunification since the publication of the joint declaration despite outsiders' vicious challenges to reunification. These successes and experience gained in it clearly prove that Koreans in the north and the south can reunify the country independently just as desired and required by the nation only when they fully discharge their responsibility and role in close unity as parties responsible for reunification. Herein lies the cause why the idea of "By our nation itself" serves as a motive force enabling all the Koreans to discharge their responsibility and role in the movement for national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The idea also serves as a source of strength enabling the Koreans to wage the movement for national reunification as a nationwide patriotic movement, the article says, stressing the need for all the Koreans to hold high the banner of "By our nation itself" and vigorously advance the movement for reconciliation, cooperation and reunification under that banner no matter how desperately the anti-reunification forces at home and abroad may work.

Respecting Human Rights Called for
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 10 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun today dedicates a signed article to the world day of human rights.
 The biggest achievement made in the struggle to build a new world in which human rights are respected is that the man-centered socialist system, the first of its kind in the world, has been established and consolidated in the DPRK, the article says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. and its allies have slandered and checked the achievements and experience gained by the DPRK and other developing countries as regards the human rights from spreading to the international community. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. and some western forces try to mock and infringe upon the sovereignty of anti-imperialist and independent countries, putting human rights over sovereignty. The U.S. is applying unjust double standards in the field of human rights while taking issue with human rights of other countries and styling itself the human rights judge which no one admits. Rigmarole on human rights made by the U.S. and some other Western forces is, in essence, the theory of overturn of system, regime change and a prelude to aggression. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They have serious human rights problems although they say this or that about "human rights" issue of other countries. The U.S. is the worst human rights abuser of the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Even in the new century the U.S. unhesitatingly committed such hideous human rights abuses as undisguised aggression on sovereign states and massacre of innocent civilians. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 That is not all. It was recently disclosed that the U.S. has operated secret prisons in European countries and CIA airplanes have used airports in those countries to carry POWs from Iraq, Afghanistan and other areas. This has sparked off a big furor worldwide. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. is now treating prisoners barbarously at its forces' concentration camps overseas including the Guantanamo naval base. 
 Like this, the U.S. is covering up its human rights abuses while faking up and taking issue with human rights of other countries. It is using them as a pretext for aggression, pressure and interference. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Human rights precisely mean the right of the state, the article says, adding that the Songun banner held high by the Koreans is greatly encouraging the world people in their efforts to build a new world in which human rights are respected in the new century.

3rd Video Meetings of Separated Families and Relatives of North and South Held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 10 (KCNA) -- The 3rd video meetings of separated families and relatives of the north and the south were held on Dec. 8 and 9.
 When the meetings started, the families and relatives of the north and the south talked to each other about the path of life covered by them and exchanged long pent-up inmost thoughts, showing photos of their families and relatives. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Those from the north side proudly told their kin from the south that they have fully enjoyed a worthwhile life under the warm care of leader Kim Jong Il and devoted themselves to building a great prosperous powerful socialist nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The separated families and relatives of the north and the south in their video meetings resolved in unison to pool their efforts to put an end to the tragedy of national division and bring earlier the day when they will live all together in happiness in the reunified country free from outside forces.
